# Agent Prompt: Open Source Network Hardware Recommendation Engine

## Project Overview

Build a full-stack web application that helps network engineers select the right vendor hardware based on their requirements. Think of it as a "Wirecutter for network gear" — an opinionated, questionnaire-driven recommendation engine.

The user answers a structured questionnaire about their network requirements. The engine scores all known products against their answers and returns ranked recommendations with reasoning. The product database is designed so community contributors can add new products with minimal friction.

---

## Questionnaire Categories

Cover at minimum these requirement dimensions:

- **Capacity** — backhaul speed (1G / 10G / 40G / 100G / 400G / 800G), uplink requirements, total interface count by type
- **Routing scale** — full BGP table support (yes/no), number of BGP peers, VRF count, route table size (IPv4/IPv6)
- **Traffic profile** — peak bandwidth (Gbps), traffic pattern (core/edge/peering/access), MPLS/segment routing needed
- **Subscriber scale** — current subscriber count, expected growth over 5 and 10 years, BNG/PPPoE/RADIUS requirements
- **Features** — EVPN, QoS complexity, multicast, telemetry/streaming, timing/PTP, MACsec
- **Operational** — preferred OS ecosystem (IOS-XR, JunOS, EOS, NOS-agnostic), automation/YANG support, OpenConfig
- **Licensing preference** — Perpetual / Subscription / No preference (see Licensing Model section below)

---

## Product Database Design

This is the most important architectural decision. Products must be defined in flat, human-readable data files (YAML or JSON) so contributors don't need to touch application code. Each product file should include:

```yaml
id: cisco-8201-32fh
vendor: Cisco
product_line: 8000 Series
model: 8201-32FH
category: core-router  # core-router | edge-router | peering-router | aggregation | access

interfaces:
  400G: 32
  100G: 0
  10G: 0
  1G: 0

capabilities:
  max_backhaul_G: 400
  full_bgp_table: true
  max_bgp_peers: 4000
  max_vrfs: 4000
  max_ipv4_routes: 4000000
  mpls: true
  segment_routing: true
  evpn: true
  bng: false
  ptp: true
  macsec: true
  openconfig: true
  streaming_telemetry: true

scale:
  max_bandwidth_Tbps: 12.8
  subscriber_scale: null  # null means N/A

os: IOS-XR

licensing:
  model: subscription  # perpetual | subscription | mixed
  notes: >
    Requires Smart Licensing. IOS-XR features (MPLS, segment routing,
    BGP scale) are individually licensed add-ons. Telemetry requires
    separate license.

notes: >
  Purpose-built silicon (Q200). Strong fit for core and peering roles.
  Not suited for BNG/subscriber use cases.

links:
  datasheet: https://...
  product_page: https://...
```

Seed the database with at least 10–15 real products across vendors (Cisco, Juniper, Nokia, Arista, Huawei) covering different tiers and use cases so the engine has enough data to demonstrate meaningful differentiation.

