## Licensing Model

Do not capture or display pricing of any kind. Licensing model is the right level of abstraction — it's durable, meaningful to ops and finance teams, and doesn't go stale the way list prices do.

Common patterns to represent across the seed products:

- **Perpetual** — pay once, own forever (Arista EOS, most whitebox NOS options)
- **Subscription** — annual renewal required, features may be gated behind tiers (Cisco Smart Licensing, Nokia SR OS feature packs)
- **Mixed** — base OS is perpetual, advanced features are subscription (Juniper Flex licensing, some Arista CloudVision add-ons)

The questionnaire should ask: *"Does your organization have a preference or policy around software licensing model?"* with options for Perpetual / Subscription / No preference — and factor that into scoring as a soft filter, not a hard disqualifier.

The results UI should surface the licensing model prominently on each recommendation card so engineers know what they're walking into before the vendor call — but never show or imply a price.

